<#
.SYNOPSIS
    This PowerShell sets the account lockout duration to 15 minutes. When enabled, it prevents brute-force password attacks on the system. This parameter specifies the amount of time that an account will remain locked after the specified number of failed logon attempts.

.NOTES
    Author          : Luka Groff
    LinkedIn        : linkedin.com/in/luka-groff/
    GitHub          : github.com/LukaGroff
    Date Created    : 2025-September-23
    Last Modified   : 2025-September-23
    Version         : 1.0
    CVEs            : N/A
    Plugin IDs      : N/A
    STIG-ID         : WN10-AC-000005

.TESTED ON
    Date(s) Tested  : 2025-September-23
    Tested By       : Luka Groff
    Systems Tested  : Windows 10
    PowerShell Ver. : 

.USAGE
    Paste the code below into powershell ISE, save it as a "script-name".ps1 and run it.
    Example syntax:
    PS C:\> .\STIG-ID-WN10-AC-000005.ps1 
#>

#COPY THE FOLLOWING:
# Must be run as Administrator

# Set Account Lockout Duration to 15 minutes
net accounts /lockoutduration:15

# Verify the setting
net accounts | findstr "Lockout"
